On 12/24/2024 at 09:57 AM, Robert Moyer wrote:
To:Christine Moyer (First Viewed: 12/24/2024 at 11:11 AM)
Subject:Re: No Response Requested
So....
I am hoping that since I did all of our Santa gifts last year and we never said anything different, I can piggyback off you this year. I brought it
up, and I think you said you would get back to me, but I have not seen anything.
I don't see Max or Elsa at all, and I have not had time to discuss this with AD. Last year, we made our own ornaments, decorated, and had a
sleepover. This year, there is nothing—not even a tree. I just don't exist anymore.
I hope you and I work together better in the new year.  Can you please let me know?
Merry Christmas to the Moyer's. So weird not to be in the family that bears my name.
robert

Hope you are having an awesome time!
